detailed-desc.p:
[in-line-formulae]X—(CH(R))nCH3 [/in-line-formulae]
wherein X represents CH3, —CH2OR1; —C(O)OR2; or —C(O)NR3R4;
R is, for each n, independently absent, H or lower aliphatic;
n is an integer from 8 to 34, such as from 10 to 24; and
R1, R2, R3 and R4 independently are selected from H and lower aliphatic. Typically, when R is lower aliphatic, R represents a branched, unbranched or cyclic lower alkyl or lower alkenyl moiety. Exemplary R groups include, without limitation, methyl, isopropyl, isobutyl, sec-butyl, cyclopentenyl, and the like.
